org.gvsig.fmap.geom.aggregate

Interface MultiPrimitive

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Aggregate, Comparable, Geometry, Iterable<Geometry>, Serializable, Shape
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MultiCurve, MultiLine, MultiPoint, MultiPolygon, MultiSolid, MultiSurface
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractMultiCurve, AbstractMultiLine, AbstractMultiPoint, AbstractMultiPolygon, AbstractMultiPrimitive, AbstractMultiSurface, BaseMultiPrimitive, BaseMultiPrimitive2D, DefaultMultiCurve, DefaultMultiSurface, MultiCurve2D, MultiCurve2DZ, MultiLine2D, MultiLine2DM, MultiLine3D, MultiLine3DM, MultiPoint2D, MultiPoint2D, MultiPoint2DM, MultiPoint2DZ, MultiPoint3D, MultiPoint3DM, MultiPolygon2D, MultiPolygon2DM, MultiPolygon3D, MultiPolygon3DM, MultiSolid2DZ, MultiSurface2D, MultiSurface3D

    public interface MultiPrimitive
extends Aggregate

    This interface is equivalent to the GM_MultiPrimitive specified in ISO 19107. MultiPrimitive is the root class for all primitive aggregates. The association role "element" shall be the set of Primitive's contained in this MultiPrimitive.

    See Also:
    ISO 19107
